30|$|The study {{included}} 23 patients undergoing elective gynecological laparoscopic procedures {{at the day}} care ambulatory gynecoendoscopic unit in Carmel Medical Center. The recruited patients were above the age of 18 and had an ASA (American Society of Anesthesiologists) physical status grade of 1 to 2. The study {{was approved by the}} hospital <b>Helsinki</b> Ethics <b>Committee</b> as well as the Israeli Ministry of Health.|$|R
